  "subject": "feat: alerting activation prep -- echo-receiver, chronic-failure + staleness alerts",
  "body": "Plan 4 Task T2S1 prework. New kind-only echo-receiver (values-gated\nechoReceiver.enabled, chart/templates/echo-receiver.yaml) stands in for a\nreal Slack webhook so the Alertmanager route/group/inhibit/receiver\npipeline (apps/infra/monitoring.yaml, separate commit) is end-to-end\ntestable without a Slack workspace.\n\nNew PrometheusRule alerts in the datalake-pipeline group:\n- WorkflowChronicFailure (>=3 Failed/Error in 7d, critical) -- the\n  E1-streak escalation the P2 Task 5 review demanded.\n- SiteSonarStale / IcebergMaintenanceStale -- trigger-staleness follow-up\n  for the two CronWorkflows the original alert set never covered\n  (P2-final follow-up). IcebergMaintenanceStale's annotation documents the\n  deferral blind spot honestly (P3-final ride-along): a chronically\n  deferring run-trino-maintenance still triggers on schedule and exits 0,\n  so no Prometheus signal in this stack (verified live: no Trino/Iceberg\n  exporter exists) can currently distinguish \"ran for real\" from\n  \"deferred\" without a new component -- deliberately not added here.\n"
}
